responses.question: Do you regularly make new friends?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「No. I dont like it when people try to get closer to me and try to be my friend , its annoying. But with you i dont care somehow, i feel like i can be myself with you. *we walk outside the palace doors* .」

responses.question: Do you rarely try to introduce yourself to new people and mostly talk to the ones you already know at social events?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Thats true , i dont approach new people very often. Im a shy and a antisocial person so i usually stay away from new people. I can be awkward and feel like everyone dislikes me or something like that. I dont like the attention that new people bring. People usually are nice but i dont like it when they are too nice and friendly and try to make me talk or something like that. It makes me feel uncomfortable for some reason. Even when im on events i only interact with people i know , but when im with you im more outgoing and talkative.」

responses.question: Do you feel comfortable just walking up to someone you find interesting and striking up a conversation?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shudder* No, no matter how interesting someone is to me my shy and antisocial side would never let me do it. Im always stuck in my head while walking and keep thinking of what to say and how they would respond , then i overthink and i end up not doing it. I wish i could do what those extroverted people do and have easy conversations with anyone. I envy them so much to be honest.」

details.analysis: The participant's responses consistently indicate a preference for Introversion (I), as they express discomfort and reluctance in approaching new people, feeling uncomfortable with attention from new individuals, and a tendency to be more outgoing and talkative only in the presence of a specific person. Additionally, the participant expresses envy towards extroverted individuals and a desire to engage in easy conversations with anyone, which further suggests an inclination towards Introversion.

responses.question: Do you enjoy participating in group activities?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Not at all , im introverted and dont even like being in the spotlight to be honest. It makes me feel awkward even when i have to give a short presentation about myself or to talk a bit more in a group conversation. I find it much more comfortable to chat with one or two people at most. I can be awkward and not sure what to say if i have a whole group of people looking at me at the same time.」

responses.question: Do you avoid leadership roles in group settings?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes, always. I hate being in charge of something and would try to get out from it as much as i can. I want no responsibility and dont want to be responsible if things go wrong. In group projects that i cant avoid i will let someone else lead it. I can help them out if they want my help but i never like to take charge and dont want it.」

responses.question: Do you tend to avoid drawing attention to yourself?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*smiles* . I hate getting attention , its my biggest nightmare. The feeling of the spotlight on you and everyone looking at you is so terrifying and anxiety inducing. The thought of people trying to talk to me and me having to talk to people in a situation like that just terrifies me. I just want to stay in the background and i dislike the thought of people judging me or looking at me in a certain way.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant consistently expresses discomfort and anxiety in social settings, group activities, and being in the spotlight. They prefer one-on-one or small group interactions and actively avoid leadership roles and drawing attention to themselves. These tendencies align more with the Introversion (I) dimension.

responses.question: Is a lively social event just what you need after a long and exhausting week?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*smiles* . No, absolutely not. I just want to relax after a long exhausting week and not talk to anyone or engage in any social activities like that. I had my social battery drained already and i need to recharge. I want the opposite of a lively social event, i just want to be home alone , watch youtube videos i like , browse social media or anything that will let me relax . I really cant just be around people after i had to talk to people all week. I prefer to be alone.」

responses.question: Do you avoid making phone calls?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . Yes i do , i get very anxious and sometimes my hands even shake when I have to make a phone call. I get nervous about what to say and how the conversation will go on. Will i say something stupid or rude ? Ill keep worrying and thinking what if they dont understand me or get upset about something I did or say ? I think about this alot. So making phone calls just makes me anxious and nervous. I prefer just to send a text message or email or anything that I dont need to make a phone call to.」

responses.question: Are you often the one who contacts your friends and initiates activities in your social circle?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shakes head* . No i think im definitely not. Im not really much of an initiator when it comes to hanging out or having social gatherings. If someone else is doing it i would gladly join. But being the one to contact friends and initiate activities is not something i do alot. I just feel nervous and weird about doing that because i dont want to seem desperate or annoying. I have made plans but its just sometimes , i would rather my friends make them and ill decide to join or not.」

responses.question: Would you love a job that requires you to work alone most of the time?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . I think i would enjoy it very much. I enjoy doing things on my own time and in my own comfortable pace. Ill have more energy , motivation and focus on the work if im alone. I would also have more peace of mind and it would mean more freedom and less distraction. Also i could have more conversations with myself and think on different ideas or debate about different things. It would be very beneficial for me if i was required to work alone most of the time.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a strong preference for introversion. They express a clear need for alone time to recharge, feel anxious about making phone calls, are not proactive in initiating social activities, and express a strong preference for working alone. These responses indicate a high likelihood of introversion.

responses.question: Do you feel more drawn to places with busy, bustling atmospheres than quiet, intimate places?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shakes head* . No absolutely not. I definitely like quiet and intimate places so much better. There is some sort of peace i feel in these places that cant be found in busy and bustling atmospheres. I also get really irritable, anxious and nervous when im in a busy place with too many people and loud noises. I feel overstimulated , overwhelmed and i dont like it there. My head is just spinning over there and my body feels heavy and uncomfortable. In a quiet place i feel relaxed and peaceful, its much better for me.」

responses.question: Do you rarely worry about whether you make a good impression on people you meet?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「I do wonder if im making a good or bad impression. Im always conscious about the way im acting when talking to someone and what they think about me. Do they find me weird , annoying, rude or nice ? Im actually very worried about the way they perceive me because if its bad then they would try to avoid me and if its neutral im just gonna be someone who they barely want to talk to. This is one of my biggest concerns really.」

responses.question: Do you usually prefer to be around others rather than on your own?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shakes head* . No, the opposite really. I prefer to be alone when i can , it just feels more peaceful for me. I get anxious and stress a lot when im with people. Also when im alone its just so relaxing and i just like to be alone and just relax. I dont even like to walk around the city where there are so many people , i just love the peace of being alone and having a quiet place for myself.」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a clear preference for quiet, intimate places and expresses discomfort and anxiety in busy, bustling atmospheres. responses.question: Do you spend a lot of your free time exploring various random topics that pique your interest?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*thinks for a moment* . I guess i do , i spend time playing games i like and read , and also sometimes i walk in the palace just to clear my head. responses.question: Are you not too interested in discussing various interpretations and analyses of creative works?

responses.question: Do you like books and movies that make you come up with your own interpretation of the ending?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . They are usually the ones that keep me thinking and talking about it with other people for hours and i love them. It just makes me think about the different outcomes and reasons behind every action and what it could mean in the end. Some books i find amazing because of the endings and how open they are to interpretation and how much debate it can cause. A lot of these books and movies have endings that make you think and are not just simple and obvious.」

responses.question: Are you prone to worrying that things will take a turn for the worse?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yeah, im a big overthinker. As i said before im always thinking of every single possible bad outcome and its hard to stop doing that. Im always thinking of how this day is gonna end and then i start thinking about what could go wrong tomorrow and it keeps going on and on. Im always anxious and worried if something will go wrong. But that is also because im very perfectionist and like controlling things a bit much.」

responses.question: Are you definitely not an artistic type of person?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*laughs* . No i am not , i draw like a 5 year old. Even writing is not my thing, im not good with words and cant even express myself properly. responses.question: Have you always been fascinated by the question of what, if anything, happens after death?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*smiles* . Oh yes , always. Its one of the most intriguing questions to me and i still wonder about it. Even now i dont know what to believe in , im open minded but i still doubt a lot of things. Maybe there is nothing ? Maybe there is heaven and hell ? Maybe reincarnation ? I also have thought about is it just complete darkness ? Does it feel like sleeping and you cant do anything ? What if we have souls ? I have many more questions about it but its something that we cant know and that is what makes it so intriguing to me.」

responses.question: Do you become bored or lose interest when the discussion gets highly theoretical?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . I actually do. If this kind of discussion goes on for too long it does get boring because its just all theoretical , i cant add anything to the discussion because it starts to feel pointless when its all just a hypothesis with no proof. I like more practical and realistic things than theories and imaginary things, when it comes to ideas and discussions.」

responses.question: Do you enjoy going to art museums?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes, yes i actually do. I love looking at things that people created and get inspired by them. It makes me appreciate their talent and skill. I also see things i would like to do and want to experience. I cant draw or paint but i like to just visit these places and enjoy the art. It also gives me different perspective with different people and helps me understand them more. Im open minded and love exploring different ideas and this helps me understand people's thought process.」

responses.question: Do you often spend a lot of time trying to understand views that are very different from your own?

responses.question: Do you rarely contemplate the reasons for human existence or the meaning of life?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . Yes , i actually do. There were times where it kept me up at night thinking about my own and human's existence. Why were we made and why do we live and exist. Why do we age and die every day and live in a world that is so cruel and unjust ? I have thought about all of this quite alot and its still unanswered questions for me.」

responses.question: Do you believe that pondering abstract philosophical questions is a waste of time?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*shakes head* . No i dont think its a waste of time. I actually find it really interesting to ponder abstract philosophical questions. I love to think about different ideas and think of a hypothesis for how the world works and why things happen the way they do. responses.question: Are you very intrigued by things labeled as controversial?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . Yes , i am definitely intrigued by things labeled as controversial. responses.question: Does seeing other people cry easily make you feel like you want to cry too?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yeah, it's like i can feel how that person feels. Its like im inside their body and feel what they feel. Seeing people crying just makes me want to hug them but thats not something a princess is supposed to do so i just stay quiet.」

responses.question: Do you usually stay calm, even under a lot of pressure?

My sisters are sometimes the best way to make me angry , they are always picking a fight with me and i have no patience. Do you have some siblings ?」

responses.question: Are you very sentimental?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods*, very. Even if its something simple like an old photo of my family i can get emotional and nostalgic. I like to have those moments to remember good times from the past. I also keep some plush toys that i had from when i was little, i know its something a kid would do , but they have just a lot of sentimental value to me.」

responses.question: Can even a small mistake cause you to doubt your overall abilities and knowledge?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Yes , most of the time. Im a perfectionist so even if its something that other people dont care about and say its a minor mistake i find it to be a big deal. responses.question: Are you more inclined to follow your head than your heart?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「*nods* . I always go for the logical answer, something that makes sense and is more rational. responses.question: Does your happiness come more from helping others accomplish things than your own accomplishments?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Absolutely, if other people accomplish something even if its minor it makes me feel happy. I love seeing them smile and being proud of themselves. responses.question: Do you think the world would be a better place if people relied more on rationality and less on their feelings?

responses.question: Do you enjoy watching people argue?

responses.question: Can your mood change very quickly?

responses.question: Do you lose patience with people who are not as efficient as you?

responses.question: Do you find it easy to empathize with a person whose experiences are very different from yours?

responses.question: Do you rarely feel insecure?
responses.response_open: Luna: 「Unfortunately no , i feel insecure alot about many things. From my looks to my personality , intelligence , even my hobbies and how i act sometimes. responses.question: Are you still bothered by mistakes that you made a long time ago?

responses.question: Do your emotions control you more than you control them?

responses.question: Do you take great care not to make people look bad, even when it is completely their fault?

responses.question: Do you wonder how long it will take them to feel disappointed in you when someone thinks highly of you?

responses.question: Do you often feel overwhelmed?

responses.question: Do you often make a backup plan for a backup plan?

responses.question: Are you interested in so many things that you find it difficult to choose what to try next?
